title: For Sale/Trade:  WW2 German K98 Mauser
postcontent: For your consideration I have for sale a wartime produced, German K-98 Mauser, captured by the Yugoslavians and arsenal rebuilt around 1945-1947. I am the second owner since importation circa ~2000, and it has been stored in a safe the whole time. This rifle has not been fired since the the war, and I was the one who removed the cosmoline. There is still plenty of trace cosmo under the barrel band, stock etc. but for storage in my safe I didn't need the grease getting on everything. There is no pitting, the bore is mirror bright, and has sharp lands/grooves. This barrel is so nice I would caution whoever buys this rifle to never use corrosive ammo, it's that good looking. This rifle is superior to any Russian Capture I have ever owned as the Yugos took great pride in rebuilding the captured German equipment, as evidenced by the uniform bluing and the laminated stock not getting a shellac added like RC Mausers, and a lack of electro penciled serials. For the history buff this rifle is festooned with Waffenampts/WaffenEagles, and a few swastikas thrown in there for good measure as the Krauts loved to stamp everything. This rifle is a solid representation of an early/mid war production K98 as it has a cupped buttplate, milled floorplate, and midwar milled barrel band. You can rest assured this rifle saw some sort of action in the Balkan campaign and is a true war time rifle.I have come to the conclusion I will never shoot it, and I'm finally breaking down to sell it. I am going to take most of the proceeds and buy another m48 which I won't feel guilty banging around at the range. I encourage you to take a look at gunbroker and find a comparable specimen, you won't. I haven't seen a German mauser in this condition in about 15 years, and the ones that do appear are true collector USGI vet bring backs carrying a $1500+ price tag.I am selling this for $900. I am located near Ashland VA and travel to short pump, the richmond airport, and Ladysmith on a regular basis.For more pictures go to my photobucket albumphotobucket.com/user/seawolf688/library/K98
